40|$|One of {{the main}} {{components}} of common agricultural policy reform is incorporating <b>agricultural</b> <b>insurance</b> schemes into the rural development policy. Subsidized <b>agricultural</b> <b>insurance</b> schemes practice shows that this policy instrument is cost-ineffective and disturbs agricultural markets in many different ways. The main {{purpose of this paper is}} to show specific character of <b>agricultural</b> <b>insurance</b> and summary of experiences with this kind of insurance, which suggest that subsidized <b>agricultural</b> <b>insurance</b> may be not the best option of assisting agricultural producers’ risk management efforts. ...|$|R
40|$|Climate change {{represents}} {{the most significant}} risk globally. The modern world has suffered enormous damage as a result. Important measures have been initiated in support of strengthening actions for disaster risk reduction. Serbia is a country exposed to various risks. The paper presents limitations of Serbian stakeholders, and the insurance market in process of reducing disaster risks. Serbian agriculture, in particular is especially vulnerable. Analysis of data {{presented in this paper}} shows {{that there is a lot}} of room for improvement. In the first part of the paper importance of natural disasters is highlighted and their impact on people and economy in general is explained. Second part of the paper presents a brief analysis of insurance sistems in Europe and Central Eastern European region, followed by an overview of Serbian <b>Insurance</b> <b>System</b> with special emphasis on non-life insurance. Third part shows catastrophe risk caused by natural disasters in the region and in Serbia. Fourth part explains the role of <b>agricultural</b> <b>insurance,</b> and explains how can <b>agricultural</b> <b>insurance</b> can be used as a new risk management tool in Serbia...|$|R
